problem_text: All cows are bovines. Some pets are cows. If something is a bovine, then it is domesticated. No domesticated animals are alligators. Ted is an aligator.
predicates:
Bovine(x) ::: x is a bovine.
Cow(x) ::: x is a cow.
Pet(x) ::: x is a pet.
Domesticated(x) ::: x is domesticated.
Alligator(x) ::: x is an alligator.
Ted(x) ::: x is Ted.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? No pet is a domesticated animal.
tests.conclusions: ¬∃x (Pet(x) ∧ Domesticated(x)) ::: No pet is a domesticated animal. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Ted is a domesticated animal.
tests.conclusions: Domesticated(ted) ::: Ted is a domesticated animal. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Ted is a bovine.
tests.conclusions: Bovine(ted) ::: Ted is a bovine. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Some pets are domesticated animals.
tests.conclusions: ∃x (Pet(x) ∧ Domesticated(x)) ::: Some pets are domesticated animals. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Some pets are domesticated animals and Ted is a bovine.
tests.conclusions: ∃x (Pet(x) ∧ Domesticated(x)) ∧ Bovine(ted) ::: Some pets are domesticated animals and Ted is a bovine. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Some pets are alligators.
tests.conclusions: ∃x (Pet(x) ∧ Alligator(x)) ::: Some pets are alligators. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Some pets are not alligators.
tests.conclusions: ∃x (Pet(x) ∧ ¬Alligator(x)) ::: Some pets are not alligators. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Ted is a pet.
tests.conclusions: Pet(ted) ::: Ted is a pet. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Ted is a bovine, then Ted is domesticated.
tests.conclusions: Ted(ted) ∧ Alligator(ted) → ¬Domesticated(ted) ::: If Ted is a bovine, then Ted is domesticated. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? All pets are domesticated.
